sql:
SELECT AVG(adj_fare) AS average_adjusted_fare
FROM airfare
WHERE airport_code = '1';

external_knowledge:
- Revenue growth rate refers to the percentage change in total revenue from one year to the next; 
- Fare growth rate refers to the percentage change in average adjusted fare from one year to the next; 
- Growth rates are calculated using the formula (current value - previous value) / previous value; 
- This calculation assumes that the revenue and fare values are non-zero to avoid division by zero errors.

